The paper deals with algorithms for graph problems with polynomially bounded edge weight functions, which suggests that it belongs to the data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-categories. The fact that the graph is planar also suggests that it could belong to the discrete mathematics (cs.DM) sub-category. The use of combinatorial techniques and algebraic subroutines suggests that it could also belong to the computational complexity (cs.CC) and graph theory (cs.GT) sub-categories.
